THE GAME
--------

  'Neutrix' is a Workbench game where the idea is to move down
coloured tiles that are located at the bottom of the game board,
by clicking on the arrows that are located under. The more tiles
with the same pattern that fall consecutively, the better it is...

  When tiles are removed, all tiles located above will fall by
one level. The vacated uppermost position of the column will be
replaced by a new tile... or a neutral block, if there is one at
the lowermost position in that column.

  Avoid placing 2 coloured tiles or more of the same type next to
each other, either one beside another or one on top of another. If
that happens, these tiles will be 'neutrified', which means that
they will become neutral blocks. If an entire column contains only
neutral blocks, the game will be over.

  Have fun!

